The discussions were given a new urgency when the delegates focused on the fact that most open issues need to be resolved before the leaders arrived to reach an agreement.
High-level representatives, such as the Indian Minister for the Environment Jairam Ramesh and the Chinese Vice-Minister, escaped their planes and raided through the corridors of the Bella Center to meet behind closed doors and press conferences to cover claims that are being negotiated during the next week.
The mere extent of the meeting -- 13,000 people are entering and leaving the conference center every day, playing guitar activists are doing night shows, in which they are making fun of the countries that they think are selling and selling, and draft contracts are handed over by hand rather than by e-mail -- is already a challenge.
